Jordan slid over to steal the ball from an unsuspecting Karl Malone, brought the ball upcourt to isolate his man and unleashed one of the smoothest crossovers in basketball history on Bryon Russell.
Of course, once Jordan drained the pull-up jumper, he stood on his toes and held the shooting form for a second too long to add the exclamation point as the Bulls took an 87-86 lead.
Jordan averaged 33.5 points and 4 rebounds in the series and won his sixth NBA Finals MVP, putting an exclamation point on the franchise’s sixth title in eight years — and his Bulls career.